The '''Kraków School of Mathematics and Astrology''' ({{lang-pl|krakowska szkoła matematyczna i astrologiczna}}) was an influential mid-to-late-15th-century group of mathematicians and astrologers at the [[Jagiellonian University|University of Kraków]] (later ''Jagiellonian University'').
==Notable members== * [[Jan of Głogów]] (1445–1507), author of widely recognized mathematical and astrological tracts * [[:pl:Marcin Biem|Marcin Biem]] (1470–1540), contributor to the [[Gregorian calendar]] * [[Marcin Bylica]] of [[Olkusz]] (1433–93), later court astrologer to King [[Matthias Corvinus of Hungary]] * [[Albert Brudzewski]] (1446–1495), teacher to notable scholars active at European universities * [[:pl:Marcin Król z Żurawicy|Marcin Król]] of [[Żurawica]] (1422–1460) * [[Nicolaus Copernicus]] (1473–1543), student at Kraków in 1491–95
==See also== * [[Kraków School of Mathematics]] * [[Polish School of Mathematics]]
